  m_QuestionText:
  - FontSize: 2
    Text: "In a scene, you want an audio effect to play as soon as the player walks
      through a door. You\u2019ve set up a trigger for this to happen, but as soon
      as you press play to test the experience, the audio plays even though the player
      is nowhere near the door. \n"
  - FontSize: 2
    Text: What might be the cause of this issue? Select one answer.
  m_Skills: Refine existing audio in a Unity project
  m_ShuffleAnswers: 1
  m_Answers:
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: The audio source must be attached to the collider itself.
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: The audio clip is set to loop.
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: "The collider isn\u2019t set to OnTrigger."
  - IsCorrect: 1
    Text: Play on Awake is checked on the audio source.
  m_FeedbackCorrect: When a new audio source is created, Play on Awake is automatically
    checked. This option must be unchecked if you wish to trigger the sound to play
    at a certain time.
  m_FeedbackIncorrect: When a new audio source is created, Play on Awake is automatically
